Banca Comerciala Romana Lends Martifer’s Prio Foods $44 Million

-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 
2011-07-07T10:14:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/banca-comerciala-romana-lends-martifer-s-prio-foods-44-million.html
Banca Comerciala Romana SA,  Romania ’s
biggest bank by assets, said it approved a loan of 31 million
euros ($44 million) to  Martifer SGPS SA (MAR) ’s Prio Foods unit, for
working capital at a new factory.  The loan falls due in 12 months and will finance the
operation of Prio Foods’ crushing unit for edible oil production
in Liehlu, southeast Romania, the bank said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Prio Foods  said in May that it had completed a
93 million-euro investment at Liehlu, where the company has
other production and storage facilities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez in Prague at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  